    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In Chinese culture, certain objects placed in tombs for the use of the deceased or as the vessels for spirits. Included are figurines of people and animals, buildings and tools, and replicas of objects in life made of precious materials, such as jewels.</Note_Text>
